The paper focuses on the task of combining unscored recommendations into a single ensemble, which is a common problem in recommender systems. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new hybridization method that combines aspects of genetic algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization problems. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves testing the performance of the proposed method on datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves proposing a new hybridization method, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
